Indonesia Stocks: Bayan Resources, Bumi Minerals, Gajah Tunggal

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-06-08T09:39:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-08/indonesia-stock-movers-bakrie-telecom-indosat-bayan-resources.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 4 p.m. Jakarta-time break.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  declined 17.13 points, or 0.5
percent, to 3,825.82, the sharpest drop since May 23.  Tire producers: PT Multistrada Arah Sarana (MASA IJ) jumped
9.5 percent to 520 rupiah, closing at a record. PT Gajah Tunggal
(GJTL IJ),  Indonesia ’s largest tire producer, increased 3.4
percent to 3,050 rupiah. The shares rose on expectations revenue
at tire producers will rise this year on higher vehicle sales
and stronger overseas demand, according to Syafrien Anwar, a
senior sales manager at PT Nusantara Capital Securities.  PT Bayan Resources (BYAN IJ), a coal producer, advanced 1.6
percent to 19,300 rupiah, a record close. The company expects
net income to more than double to as much as 2.02 trillion
rupiah ($237 million) this year as coal production and sales
increase,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing Soedjoko Tirtosoekotjo, a director at the company. Tirtosoekotjo couldn’t
be reached when called at his office.  PT Bumi Resources Minerals (BRMS IJ), an Indonesian mining
company, gained 4 percent to 780 rupiah, the highest close since
its December trading debut. Bumi Minerals expects iron-ore
production at its Mauritania mine to start in the first quarter
of 2012, Herwin Hidayat vice president for  investor relations ,
said by telephone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  